commit.message: Prepare for 4.20 release

Added basic CMake support (#66)

This will enable package managers and projects that relies on CMake,
like [CPM](https://github.com/cpm-cmake/CPM.cmake) to add SimpleIni
as a dependency easily. Note that it does not enable building the test
harness using CMake, this is still via the Makefile.

Signed-off-by: Vinícius Ferrão <vinicius@ferrao.net.br>

- Allow flags to be provided by the environment
- Use pkg-config for gtest discovery instead of using nonportable
  hardcoded flags
- Name target after the file it produces
